Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udaeanorendarion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daeanor Endarion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/picon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/5/01 3:46:29 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.monmouth.com/~dhawthorne/everqst/ppic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much would you pay for Markar's Discord?</span><hr size=1> I don't use stuns all that much, wouldn't pay more than 500pp for it. When I needed Plainsight (much more useful to me personally, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> always</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have it up), the first person I met who was selling it wanted 2k. I laughed and said &quot;no thanks.&quot; They stuttered a bit about how rare it was, and how useful, and I replied, &quot;That's all true, but it's not worth that much to *me*. Good luck with it.&quot; The very next day, I bought it for 150pp. So I say the same about MD - I won't pay any more than 500pp. Eventually, I will get the drop or find it cheaper. In the meanwhile, I won't encouraged spell-price gougers, and will do without.<br>
<br>
Here's an even better one, the other day, someone tried to sell me Group TL for 5k - I got a real good laugh out of that one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p><table><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#cc0000 strength=1)><font size=2 color=#ffff00 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Daeanor Endarion of the Rathe</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaario.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ma ar io</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/11/01 9:51:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How much would you pay for Markar's Discord?</span><hr size=1> <br>
In my opinion, this spell is spellbook filler only.  I have never used it except to test it out a few times.<br>
<br>
Basically, this spell does draught damage with Tishan's Dischord stun attached.  For more mana.<br>
<br>
Generally, if I want to stun something (to prevent a heal or gate, or just to save the healer some mana), I use Tishan's Discord.  <br>
<br>
When I'm trying to prevent something from gating, I usually stun with Tishan's.  In a case like that, the casting time on the stun is the most important factor.  It doesn't help any if you got the stun off 0.5 seconds AFTER the mob gated.<br>
<br>
Looking at the cast time, it is 2.25 seconds for Tishan's, and 3.30 seconds for Markar's.  Over a full second longer for Markar's.  A very long time, considering the casting time for gate is only 5 seconds.<br>
<br>
Caster's realm has the stun length at 8 seconds for Tishan's, and 5 seconds for Markar's.  Graffe's has the stun length at 5 seconds for both.<br>
<br>
From my personal tests, I remember the two being similar if not the same - so no advantage for either spell here.  Also, the recovery time for Tishan's is better than that for Markar's. (18 versus 24 seconds)<br>
<br>
On the other hand, if I need to do damage and drop a mob fast, I have several draughts to pick from...all of which have serious mana effeciency advantages over Markar's.<br>
<br>
In conclusion, I wouldn't pay anything more than I would for a similarly useless spell - maybe 100pp for the thrill of filling up your spellbook?  <br>
<br>
Perhaps there is an advantage here I have overlooked...anyone see something I missed?<br>
<br>
-Ma`ar<br>
